 have provided an exit option in the Malay and Muslim majority nation state. As Malaysia modernizes, there are growing concerns by certain segments of the country's ethnic Chinese Buddhist population to separate Buddhism from popular Chinese religions. Nevertheless, these reformist groups face counterforces from traditional Chinese religionists within the context of the cultural complexity of the Chinese belief system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBuddhismzMalaysia. 0aChinesezMalaysiaxHistory. 4aAsian Studies. 4aContemporary Society. 4aReligion and Theology. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh  aBuddhist modernism.  aChinese religions.  aMalaysian studies.  aTaiwan.  areligious transnationalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978904855183540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048551835423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048551835/original  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL